node.text:
Abercrombie recently launched a new initiative called The Equity Project, an initiative dedicated to racial and social justice. As a part of this new initiative, we launched an IGTV series called “A&F Conversations” for the adults brand,  and “Hanging out with Abercrombie” for the Kids brand, which both focus on addressing important topics on race and equality by utilizing voices of influential people to help to create change.

 

November is Native American Heritage Month, and we know that Indigenous people are not represented enough in marketing & advertising. We would be honored to have you create a video for our “Hanging out with Abercrombie” series to bring attention to your work as a water commissioner and other issues in the indigenous community. We think that you would be an AMAZING role model to kids that follow our brand, as well as for the parents that follow us so they encourage their children to be more aware of social justice issues at a young age. @abercrombie @abercrombiekids

node.text: Attended a peaceful March July 1, 2021 from Indigenous Services Canada to Parliament Hill.  We marched to honour the children that didn’t make it or and their graves have been discovered in unmarked graves, for the families who never got to see their loved ones, for the MMIW, for our Human Rights, for the injustices to our people, for the broken promises, for the land, for the water, for the future. This is only the beginning! #bringthemhome #wearestillhere #nomorestolensisters #nomoregenocide #idlenomore #granddaughterofasurvivor #daughterofasurvivor  #waterislife #anishinaabe #anishinabeknation

node.text:
as an indigenous woman with a platform i felt it is important to speak up and spread awareness. 
this is not only a muslim cause, it is a humanitarian cause. to remain silent about killing and injuring women and children is inhumane. just because this is not happening to you or in your country, it does not mean that you should not speak up about it. by choosing to stay silent, you are choosing the side of the oppressor. any decent human being should stand in solidarity with palestine. 🇵🇸❤️✊#freepalestine #freegaza (Artwork by @bomgiizhik, borrowed)
